    PPM9.41

      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      ExternalWorkItem computeEffortBreakdown()
      This method will not be called durng sync, but you can call it to compute Total Effort from Effort Breakdown.
      It will return a new ExternalWorkItem object where total effort is computed from breakdown without modifying this one.
      ExternalWorkItemEffortBreakdown getEffortBreakDown()
      Daily breakdown of the Effort for this work item.
      java.lang.String getErrorMessage()
      If an error occurs when retriving time information from the external application, you can have this method return an error (or warning) message that will be displayed on the user screen.
      By default, returns null (no error message).
      TimeSheetLineAgileEntityInfo getLineAgileEntityInfo() 
      java.lang.String getName()
      Time sheet line name from external application This property will be mapped to PPM time sheet line work item name.

    • Method Detail

      • getName

        public java.lang.String getName()
        Time sheet line name from external application This property will be mapped to PPM time sheet line work item name.
        Returns:
        Name

      • getTotalEffort

        public java.lang.Double getTotalEffort()
        Work item total effort from external application for this work item. If it returns null, it will be computed automatically from getEffortBreakDown() values.
        If both this and getEffortBreakDown() return null, this will be set to 0.
        Returns:
        Total Effort for this work item (in Hours)

      • getEffortBreakDown

        public ExternalWorkItemEffortBreakdown getEffortBreakDown()
        Daily breakdown of the Effort for this work item. If set to null, we'll consider that no time is logged against this timesheet.
        Returns:
        Effort breakdown of this timesheet line per day.

      • getErrorMessage

        public java.lang.String getErrorMessage()
        If an error occurs when retriving time information from the external application, you can have this method return an error (or warning) message that will be displayed on the user screen.
        By default, returns null (no error message).
        Returns:
        An error message string, if something went wrong.

      • getLineAgileEntityInfo

        public TimeSheetLineAgileEntityInfo getLineAgileEntityInfo()
        Returns:
        Some meta data on the Timesheet line (IDs of entity imported in this line) that will be used to auto-relate this line with a PPM Project or Task.
        The returned TimeSheetLineAgileEntityInfo must have a project ID set for auto-match to work correctly, as the list of potential matching tasks will depend on the project ID.

      • computeEffortBreakdown

        public ExternalWorkItem computeEffortBreakdown()
        This method will not be called durng sync, but you can call it to compute Total Effort from Effort Breakdown.
        It will return a new ExternalWorkItem object where total effort is computed from breakdown without modifying this one.
